  <description type="morphology">Plants to 2 dm; roots elongate, fleshily woody. Stems ± erect, simple or branching,
    sometimes suffrutescent. Leaves sessile; blade terete, sometimes slightly broadened at base, to
    5 cm. Inflorescences cymose, much overtopping leaves; peduncle scapelike, to 15 cm. Flowers
    usually pedicellate, sometimes sessile or subsessile; sepals deciduous or sometimes persistent,
    ovate, to 4.5 mm, apex sometimes purplish, acuminate-cornate, thickened; petals light pink to
    purplish, elliptic to obovate, to 7 mm; stamens (4–)5(–6); stigma 1, subcapitate, sometimes
    stigmas 3-lobed, or 3, triangular. Capsules ellipsoid or sometimes ovoid, sometimes obtusely
    trigonous, 3–5 mm. Seeds without arcuate ridges, 0.8–1 mm. 2n = 24, 48.</description>
